  "summary": "Saint Petersburg, formerly known as Petrograd (Петроград) and later Leningrad (Ленинград), is the second-largest city in Russia, after Moscow, the nation's capital. Situated on the Neva River at the head of the Gulf of Finland on the Baltic Sea, its area of \n1,439 square kilometers (556 sq mi) renders it the smallest administrative division of Russia by area.",
